
---


@startuml

class Song {
  -title: String
  -year: int
  -length: int
  -genre: String
  -artist: Artist
  -id: String
}

class Artist {
  -name: String
  -dateOfBirth: Date
  -websiteURL: String
  -id: String
}

class User {
  -id: String
  -name: String
  -address: String
  -type: UserType
}

enum UserType {
  REGULAR
  BUSINESS
}

class BusinessUser {
  -vatNumber: String
  -user: User
}

class RegularUser {
  -user: User
}

class MusicItem {
  -title: String
  -artist: Artist
  -id: String
}

class Single {
  -type: "SINGLE"
  -musicItem: MusicItem
}

class Hit {
  -type: "HIT"
  -musicItem: MusicItem
  -trackNumber: int
}

class Album {
  -title: String
  -hits: List<Hit>
  -id: String
}

class Purchase {
  -user: RegularUser
  -item: MusicItem
  -purchaseDate: Date
}

class Suggestion {
  -fromUser: RegularUser
  -toUser: RegularUser
  -album: Album
  -suggestionDate: Date
}

' Relationships

Song "1" -- "1" Artist : belongsTo
User "1" -- "1" BusinessUser : isA
User "1" -- "1" RegularUser : isA
BusinessUser "1" -- "1" Single : canUpload
RegularUser "1" -- "1" Single : canBuy
RegularUser "1" -- "1" Album : canBuy
Album "1" -- "1" Hit : contains
Hit "1" -- "1" Song : isA
Single "1" -- "1" Song : isA
Purchase "1" -- "1" RegularUser : madeBy
Purchase "1" -- "1" MusicItem : purchased
Suggestion "1" -- "1" RegularUser : from
Suggestion "1" -- "1" RegularUser : to
Suggestion "1" -- "1" Album : suggests

@enduml

---

### 📌 **Explanation of Key Elements**

- **Song**: Represents a song with title, year, length, genre, and artist.
- **Artist**: Contains name, date of birth, and website URL.
- **User**: Base class for users with ID, name, address, and type (regular or business).
- **UserType**: An `enum` defining two user types.
- **BusinessUser**: Extends `User` and adds VAT number.
- **RegularUser**: Extends `User`.
- **MusicItem**: Base class for items that can be bought or uploaded.
- **Single & Hit**: Subclasses of `MusicItem`, representing different types of songs.
- **Album**: A collection of hits (not singles), with track numbers.
- **Purchase**: Records when a regular user buys a music item.
- **Suggestion**: Allows regular users to suggest albums to others based on behavior.

---

### 📝 Notes:
- All relationships are modeled using associations.
- The diagram supports inheritance (e.g., `BusinessUser` and `RegularUser` extend `User`).
- It reflects the requirement that **a song must belong to exactly one artist**, and **the combination of song and artist is unique**.
- **Business users can only upload singles**, while **regular users can buy both singles and albums**.
- **Suggestions are made by regular users to other regular users** based on similar behavior.

